caption: One of the nicest patios in DC to sip wine! And it's all about the brunch - cinnamon rolls + bagels w/ lox + rose + patio = heaven. Also, shout out to Leah and Jordan who are delights.
great food and drinks!
Amazing food, amazing service. One of my favorite restaurants in D.C.!
Ohhhh hands down the best cinnamon buns in DC😙
The breakfast burrito and cinnamon rolls were fantastic. They did great wine specials for International Women's Day featuring Women winemakers. I can't wait to come back.
Excellent service and food 👍
We had a great Valentine's Day dinner.  Intimate cozy setting.  Good drinks and great food.

Went for brunch and the food was so good. Vegetarian friendly. Looks like it would also be a great spot for dinner and sitting outside when it's warm. They pride themselves on the homemade biscuits, but I do have to say that it was dry and had no flavor. I'm from the south and have high expectations, so it might just be me, but I wouldn't get one again. Bottomless mimosas come at a steep price at $16.
Yummy brunch spot with excellent service
Good food. Nice neighborhood spot...when it's open.
Great neighborhood wine bar

An exceptional neighborhood bistro! As soon as I walked in I could tell this spot was a local gem. Everyone within was smiling and chatting happily. A few tables had food but most of the patrons seemed to only have drinks. We started with a couple delicious cocktails that they had on tap and finished off with a delightful Spanish Tempranillo. The bartender was a joy to talk to and the atmosphere was splendid. I’m guaranteed to return!
Great neighborhood place

This is a fantastic brunch spot, especially if you are looking for bottomless options. They offer a bottomless rosé, which is super unique and also quite dangerous (pace yourself!). It’s a great place to come with a smaller group and has indoor-outdoor seating. The food is also really great!
Good neighborhood food and drinks. Small menu done well.
Wonderful selection of wines. Especially the woman made prosecco! Food is glorious! Zucchini bread AND.THE.BUTTER! THE 💃💃💃💃💃💃💃💃💃💃

A local patron, I’ve been to Tyber Creek since they opened and several times over the past year. During those visits, they usually were very attentive and seemed to value their patrons. We generally have drinks and dinners and while a bit expensive, both have been great in the past.  Today the staff and servers were very attentive but it was hard to overcome the bad taste in my mouth after their hostess held a table at opening (when no one was in the restaurant other than staff and I). She snidely deemed “reserved” required my mom to be wheeled to the other end of the restaurant which was very hard for her.(Note: the table remained empty until after we left).  Ah well. More wine and dine venues pop up every week in Eckington, NoMA and Brookland and I’m sure they and other restaurants nearby will want our patronage more than that in the future. So those are where we will go moving forward.
Brunch was great! I had the breakfast platter during Sunday brunch! Didn’t wait at all for a table outside. Beautiful way to start my Sunday and enjoy the summer weather😊😊☺️☺️
Friendly staff, good food, and a great wine list. Their weekend happy hour is also an awesome feature.
Food was great, very fun atmosphere. Friendly staff
Food was outstanding. Nick totally took care of our every need. Have already recommended it to coworkers.
Friendly service, good food St a reasonable price

Gosh I love this place. The owner is so sweet and the food great. They did such a great job changing this place from a lack-luster space into something that really adds to Bloomingdale. Hope you all have long lasting success. Everyone should come for a glass of wine and some food on the patio.

Service was extremely bad. Waiter forgot about my table at least three different times. I had to physically walk up to him to ask him to take our order after he went and took orders from two other tables that arrived after. Waited 45 mins for my food only to have the wrong thing brought out THEN waited another twenty minutes to be told that the item I ordered was no longer available.  Was very excited about this place and was super disappointed with how it turned out. Only actually had the chance to eat the cinnamon rolls which whole lauded as “their most popular item” was wholly lackluster. Didn’t taste like anything that I couldn’t have gotten from the fridge aisle in the grocery store.

Thrice, now...  First was for brunch with my brother and his girlfriend (Manhattanites and service industry veterans) and two date nights.  At brunch four of us rendered the existence of a plate of cinnamon roles plausibly deniable in minutes. Warm with gooey icing and just... gone, cinnamon roll, gone. I followed with an eggs Benedict cooked to just-runny-enough-eggs perfection.  At dinner My girlfriend and I have split Tyber’s version of a charcuterie board (can’t remember what they called it), followed by three more appetizers including a mussels in soup-esque garlic sauce which we found ourselves drinking post mussels...  There’s nothing less than sinfully delicious in their menu; a combination of tradition and innovation. French-pressed coffee is the smoothest you’ll likely ever have it.  Oh, and the service isn’t just good, it’s above and beyond. It’s so good, in fact, that you’ll forget you’re in D.C.
Big fan of the biscuits - excellent portions and great service on the bottomless mimosas.  Can't wait to come back again!
Really great service and food. Best brunch I've had in DC.
Good place to wait for your red hen reservation.  Good wines. Halloumi was good, as was the concoction that was similar to a French onion soup without the soup part.
Love their urban casual vibe and happy hour. Staff are always courteous and working together.
Nice quiet wine bar in Bloomingdale. Great low key escape after a tough day for a nice drink and meat/cheese plate. Friendly staff and weekend happy hour.
Super cute wine bar with a great menu. Definitely worth a try if you are in the neighborhood.
Neighborhood wine bar done right.
Fantastic, friendly, attentive service. Great for business conversations. Quiet + good lighting.
Great place
Food was excellent. Great wine list, fantastic atmosphere!!

Wouldve given 5 stars (food is always great!) but my server (with the bangs) threw my boxed food out within 5 mins of us leaving. We literally walked down the street, came back and then she said oh I threw it out. Like seriously? Having experience in hospitality, you dont really throw out a full box of food- u kind of wait a little to see if they would come back. Yeap there goes half of my frittata and half of my bf's smoked salmon benedict, literally worth a full meal.   Thank you my amazing server you are so quick with throwing my food out but u took forever to bring me my straw so I can drink my bloody Mary.
Great to have a place open for lunch
The service was great, very friendly staff and manager. Tried the filled dates and Halloumi cheese, and both tasted delicious.

4th visit. Service is always great; it's obvious they take what they do seriously.  Food is always tasty; some of the dinner options are truly great. Space is stylish and very clean. Inside is small, but the noise level is good. Outside patio is exceptional for the area.
Stuffed Dates.  .  .   ADDICTIVE!   Over all, super funky fresh joint!
Great wines, awesome seasonal menus, and fun people!
Great food, very good service as well.
Love this place. New to area. Great food. Very patient staff. Very CLEAN :-) drinks were on point. Will definitely be back!
Great food! Friendly staff. Great drink selection. The best patio in Bloomingdale. Brunch here is great too!
Wine is great, food is fancy (pricey) and tastes so-so.  On the expensive side (even for happy hour).

Decidedly meh. Nothing impressive on the menu. The brussel sprouts were underwhelming. I had a flat bread that I swear I had at a bar Louie once (pro tip, bar Louie is disappointing too). It's expensive. They do have the lovely patio that their predecessor Rustik installed, so there's that.
Great spot for brunch, with a super friendly staff!  You have to get the cinnamon rolls....so good!

Hey folks! Tyber Creek Wine Bar has tasty food. However, you'll be paying more than you think you should for this food. I enjoyed the roasted half chicken. However, the seasonings and sides were all pretty simple. Easy enough to make the same at home for quite less. Don't consider wine; way over priced, even for DC. Nice to pop in for a drink maybe, but a dinner experience will cost too much.
Excellent food and drinks
Solid little spot in Bloomingdale which replaces Rustik Tavern. A little fancier than the other spots in town aside from Red Hen.
Excellent staff and location. Perfect people watching and eggs. Happy it was recommended.
Excellent location, food and service!  Intimate setting, and great vibe inside...can't wait to come back during warmer weather and sit outside!
Adorable wine bar with a good happy hour and patio

The restaurant is nice and the staff is very friendly. The outside seating area was beautiful and they had lights set up which made the atmosphere lovely. The food was subpar and pricey and nothing was worth remembering, even the  bread was bad. Although they had some sort of jam spread and that was tasty. The end, if it weren't for the ambiance and decor I would've given it a 2 star rating.
Lovely little wine bar. We sat outside with our kids and had a great dinner.

Came in on a Tuesday evening for an impromptu date with my mom and we loved it! Shared the PEI Mussels (amaze), stuffed piquillo peppers (I’m stealing the recipe), halibut (YUM) and braised lamb (so tender). Ambience is great and staff was hustling.  Can’t wait to come back!
Hip wine bar and restaurant with great vegetarian options. Fantastic for brunch, when it's not too busy. Large patio space is perfect for spring/fall.
Good neighborhood bar with a quality wine selection.
We enjoyed the menu and it was quiet
Great brunch menu, fresh ingredients deliciously prepared, outdoor seating, endless mimosas--what's not to love?

With a spinning wood-fire oven in the background, the atmosphere inside is relaxing, hip, and clean. Nice outdoor patio but nothing out of the ordinary. Staff is friendly and attentive. I was pleasantly surprised by how good the food was (stuffed dates and house bread are 100%.)
Great neighborhood spot for a tasty, casual bite. Excellent wine list and good "craft" cocktails.
Solid happy hour and neighborhood vibe

Tyber Creek is a bright oasis in the already cool neighborhood of Bloomingdale. Just off the main street, Tyber Creek Wine Bar and Kitchen is a restaurant with a bar, outdoor seating, and indoor dining. My wife and I met a colleague here for Sunday brunch and left impressed.  We went at 1PM for brunch (Brunch ends at 3PM) and we didn't need a reservation. We were seated at one of their wooden booths. Of course we started with the cast iron cinnamon rolls. Five giant cinnamon rolls come out warm from the oven with the cream cheese frosting slightly melting down the sides. It's mouth watering!  For our main course, I ordered the asparagus frittata. If you want a veggie forward dish, order this. It was good as frittatas come. My wife ordered the shakshuka and enjoyed it. My colleague ordered the bibb lettuce salad with chicken and it was filling!  On top of the food, the service was attentive and the owners even came over to say hi. They are super nice making the environment even more bright!
Great new place. Moved into the spot where Rustico was, pretty solid upgrade.
Grate food !

I was only in town for a few days - so glad I picked TC for dinner.  Yum!
Wow, so impressed. Great food, very friendly staff and awesome atmosphere. Can't believe they just opened based on how smooth our experience was. We will definitely be back!
Great food, great drinks, great service! Highly recommend!
